author: Nic White For Daily Mail Australia
title: Victoria man David Morabito killed in water-skiing race | Daily Mail Online
text: Father-of-two killed when his boat flips during 210km/h water-skiing race - leaving four other people injured David Morabito, 50, killed when his boat flipped during a water-skiing race Four others were injured at the Southern 80 event in northern Victoria He is the sixth person to die in the 210km/h race since 2006 The race was called off for the day out of respect to Mr Morabito Published: 08:16 GMT, 12 February 2017 | Updated: 10:32 GMT, 12 February 2017 40 shares comments A father-of-two died and four others were badly injured in a water-skiing race day on the Murray River in northern Victoria. David Morabito, 50, was killed when his boat the '2 Ironic', travelling at up to 210km/h, flipped at Horseshoe Bend while he was driving. The the other person in the boat was also injured along with the skier it was towing. Father-of-two David Morabito, 50, died and four others were badly injured in a water-skiing race day on the Murray River in northern Victoria He was killed when his boat the '2 Ironic' (pictured at a different race), travelling at up to 210km/h, flipped at Horseshoe Bend while he was driving The Southern 80 event was called off for the day out of respect for Mr Morabito, and for the incident to be investigated. Ski Racing Australia chairman Paul Robertson confirmed the Grose Vale, NSW, man's death in the crash at 1.20pm on Sunday. RELATED ARTICLES
